# Antigravity — {{REPO_NAME}} Agent Instructions

Antigravity (`agy`) entry point. Shared repo rules: [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) (Codex uses that file as its primary entry).

## What Antigravity reads

| Asset | Path | Role |
|-------|------|------|
| Context | [GEMINI.md](GEMINI.md) | Always-loaded instructions (this file) |
| Context | [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) | Shared governance |
| Project CLI settings | [.gemini/settings.json](.gemini/settings.json) | `context.fileName`, `skills.enabled`, `hooksConfig.enabled` |
| Workspace hooks | [.agents/hooks.json](.agents/hooks.json) | PreToolUse hard gate on implementation writes (when executor supports it) |
| Mutation gate | `{{MUTATION_HOOK_SCRIPT}}` | Calls configured `verify-mutation-hook` command |
| Workspace skills | [.agents/skills/](.agents/skills/) | On-demand skills (`SKILL.md` per folder) |
| User CLI settings | `~/.gemini/antigravity-cli/settings.json` | Model, permissions, trusted workspaces |

Antigravity does **not** read `.codex/settings.toml`, `.codex/hooks/`, or any `.gemini/settings.toml`.

## Codebase policy

Read [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) before feature work.

- **Repo boundary.** Work only in `{{REPO_ROOT}}`. Scratch: `{{SCRATCH_ROOT}}/<short-slug>/`.
- **Architecture and product rules** live in project docs — not in this file.

## Mandatory skills

Canonical skill content: `.cursor/skills/`. Antigravity discovers copies via `.agents/skills/`.

| Skill | Antigravity path | When |
|-------|------------------|------|
| `gap-closure-contract` | [.agents/skills/gap-closure-contract/](.agents/skills/gap-closure-contract/) | After gap analysis + user approval, before plan edits or implementation |
| `task-registry-flow` | [.agents/skills/task-registry-flow/](.agents/skills/task-registry-flow/) | Plan activation, status, deferrals, handoff |

**Self-heal broken skill symlinks:**

```bash
mkdir -p .agents/skills
cd .agents/skills
ln -sf ../../.cursor/skills/gap-closure-contract gap-closure-contract
ln -sf ../../.cursor/skills/task-registry-flow task-registry-flow
```

## Plan activation (before code edits)

After user-approved gap closure:

1. Write or refresh `docs/plans/<short-slug>.md` with per-gap `- Behavioral:` lines, `## Validation Plan`, and one fenced `## Task Manifest` TOML block.
2. Manifest: `[[behaviors]]` with runnable `confirmation` commands; each `[[tasks]]` row links `behavior_ids`.
3. `{{TASK_REGISTRY_CLI}} activate docs/plans/<short-slug>.md`
4. Confirm tasks in `docs/task-registry.toml` with matching `source_plan_hash_sha256`.
5. Only then edit implementation files listed in active task targets.

**Hard gate:** when the project executor implements mutation verification, `.agents/hooks.json` blocks unbound implementation writes. Test with your executor's `verify-mutation` / `verify-mutation-hook` commands.

Handoff: `{{TASK_REGISTRY_CLI}} report <plan_id>`; archive completed when supported.

## Governance reminders

- **Spec authority:** {{AUTHORITY_ORDER}}. On conflict, ask.
- **Registry:** use `{{TASK_REGISTRY_CLI}}` opcodes; typed validation via `validate`.
- **Deferrals:** `TASK_DEFER` via registry CLI `defer`; requires `deferral_governance_basis` + `reactivation_condition`.

## Verify in Antigravity

Run `agy` in this repo, then `/skills` — expect `gap-closure-contract` and `task-registry-flow`. Hooks load from `.agents/hooks.json` when `hooksConfig.enabled` is true in `.gemini/settings.json`.
